CatDescriptText: Juanita Carter, practical nurse, 347 Ladson Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1959, pg. 6 with question: "With Mayor Lawrence performing his duties as Governor in Harrisburg, do you believe the Democratic party in Pittsburgh will be weakened by his absence?" answer reads: "No, I don't think so.  Mayor Lawrence has done a good job locally.  But there will be someone to come along to take his place."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Juanita Carter wearing earrings and felt coat with large light colored fur collar, holding dark handbag over left wrist, standing with hands clasped together on sidewalk with other people and building with ribbed metal wall and large window
